---
title: Spicy-Sweet Turkey Stir-Fry Rice Bowls with Gochujang Sauce, Pickled Cabbage & Sesame Seeds
description: New to gochujang sauce? This colorful stir-fry is the perfect introduction! Gochujang is a Korean paste made from chili peppers—so as you can imagine, a little goes a long way! We sweeten it up here with sesame dressing, add a dash of Sriracha for tang, then use it to coat browned turkey with broccoli, cauliflower, and carrots. Ponzu rice and pickled cabbage are the perfect sides to mellow out all those punchy flavors... and there you have it. Nice to meet you, gochujang!
